Andrew Chan, 21, and Myuran Sukumaran, 24, were caught trying to smuggle more than eight kilograms of heroin out of Indonesia .
Their first meeting was at a party in 2002 but they were disillusioned by their jobs .
They were lured into drug smuggling roles by the promised riches .
But after all their legal appeals and pleas for clemency have been rejected .
The death penalty has never left the table for Chan, who is the son of Chinese immigrants .